      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The 5-business-day reactive track is the tightest reasonable lead time: one day to compute impact, one day for finance review, one day for notifications to reach teams, and two days for teams to update budget alerts. Going faster risks budget surprises; going slower means charging teams the wrong rate for weeks."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Price Changes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Price change detection should run automatically \u2014 provider pricing pages change without notice. Poll a versioned price registry daily and compare against the current rate card's provider prices."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass PriceChangeEvent:\n    model_id: str\n    old_input_per_million: float\n    new_input_per_million: float\n    old_output_per_million: float\n    new_output_per_million: float\n    detected_at: date\n    source: str   # \"provider_announcement\" | \"invoice_diff\" | \"api_poll\"\n\n    @property\n    def input_delta_pct(self) -> float:\n        if self.old_input_per_million == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return (self.new_input_per_million - self.old_input_per_million) / self.old_input_per_million\n\n    @property\n    def output_delta_pct(self) -> float:\n        if self.old_output_per_million == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return (self.new_output_per_million - self.old_output_per_million) / self.old_output_per_million\n\n    @property\n    def max_delta_pct(self) -> float:\n        return max(abs(self.input_delta_pct), abs(self.output_delta_pct))\n\n    @property\n    def severity(self) -> str:\n        if self.max_delta_pct >= 0.20:\n            return \"HIGH\"    # \u2265 20% change \u2014 reactive update required\n        if self.max_delta_pct >= 0.05:\n            return \"MEDIUM\"  # 5\u201320% \u2014 fold into next quarterly review\n        return \"LOW\"         # < 5% \u2014 note only\n\ndef detect_price_changes(\n    old_prices: list,\n    new_prices: list,\n    threshold: float = 0.01,   # ignore changes smaller than 1%\n) -> list[PriceChangeEvent]:\n    old_by_model = {p.model_id: p for p in old_prices}\n    events = []\n    for np in new_prices:\n        op = old_by_model.get(np.model_id)\n        if op is None:\n            continue\n        input_delta = abs(np.input_per_million_usd - op.input_per_million_usd) / max(op.input_per_million_usd, 1e-9)\n        output_delta = abs(np.output_per_million_usd - op.output_per_million_usd) / max(op.output_per_million_usd, 1e-9)\n        if max(input_delta, output_delta) >= threshold:\n            events.append(PriceChangeEvent(\n                model_id=np.model_id,\n                old_input_per_million=op.input_per_million_usd,\n                new_input_per_million=np.input_per_million_usd,\n                old_output_per_million=op.output_per_million_usd,\n                new_output_per_million=np.output_per_million_usd,\n                detected_at=date.today(),\n                source=\"api_poll\",\n            ))\n    return events"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Computing Team Impact Before Notification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Never send a notification without attaching a concrete impact estimate. Teams cannot prepare without knowing their exposure. The impact report uses trailing 3-month token usage, extrapolated to monthly and annual figures, sorted by absolute annual delta."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass TeamImpactRow:\n    team: str\n    feature: str\n    monthly_tokens_m: float      # millions\n    old_monthly_cost_usd: float\n    new_monthly_cost_usd: float\n\n    @property\n    def delta_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.new_monthly_cost_usd - self.old_monthly_cost_usd\n\n    @property\n    def delta_pct(self) -> float:\n        if self.old_monthly_cost_usd == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.delta_usd / self.old_monthly_cost_usd\n\n    @property\n    def annual_delta_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.delta_usd * 12\n\ndef render_impact_table(rows: list[TeamImpactRow]) -> str:\n    rows_sorted = sorted(rows, key=lambda r: abs(r.annual_delta_usd), reverse=True)\n    lines = [\n        \"Rate Card Impact Analysis\",\n        f\"{'Team':<20} {'Feature':<20} {'Old/mo':>10} {'New/mo':>10} {'Delta':>10} {'Ann. Delta':>12}\",\n        \"-\" * 84,\n    ]\n    for r in rows_sorted:\n        sign = \"+\" if r.delta_usd >= 0 else \"\"\n        lines.append(\n            f\"{r.team:<20} {r.feature:<20} \"\n            f\"${r.old_monthly_cost_usd:>8.2f} ${r.new_monthly_cost_usd:>8.2f} \"\n            f\"{sign}{r.delta_pct:>8.1%} ${r.annual_delta_usd:>+10.0f}\"\n        )\n    total_annual = sum(r.annual_delta_usd for r in rows)\n    lines += [\"-\" * 84, f\"{'TOTAL ANNUAL IMPACT':<52} ${total_annual:>+10.0f}\"]\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Notification Templates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two notification templates cover the two tracks. Both share the same structure: what changed, the quantified impact, required actions, and a pointer to the new rate card. The reactive template is more urgent; the quarterly template includes a fuller timeline."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass NotificationChannel(Enum):\n    EMAIL  = \"email\"\n    SLACK  = \"slack\"\n    TICKET = \"ticket\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass RateCardNotification:\n    subject: str\n    body_md: str\n    channels: list[NotificationChannel]\n    recipients: list[str]     # email addresses or Slack channel IDs\n    send_at: date\n\ndef build_reactive_notification(\n    events: list[PriceChangeEvent],\n    impact_rows: list[TeamImpactRow],\n    new_effective_date: date,\n) -> RateCardNotification:\n    \"\"\"Build the notification for a reactive rate card update.\"\"\"\"\n    affected_models = \", \".join(e.model_id for e in events)\n    high_severity = [e for e in events if e.severity == \"HIGH\"]\n\n    total_annual = sum(r.annual_delta_usd for r in impact_rows)\n    sign = \"increase\" if total_annual >= 0 else \"decrease\"\n\n    body = f\"\"\"## Rate Card Update \u2014 Effective {new_effective_date}\n\n**Trigger:** Provider price change detected for: {affected_models}\n\n**What changed:**\n{chr(10).join(f\"- {e.model_id}: input {e.input_delta_pct:+.1%}, output {e.output_delta_pct:+.1%}\" for e in events)}\n\n**Impact on your team:** See the full impact table in the FinOps dashboard.\nEstimated portfolio-wide annual {sign}: **${abs(total_annual):,.0f}**\n\n**Action required:**\n- {\"Review and update your team budget in the next 5 business days.\" if high_severity else \"No immediate action required \u2014 folded into next quarterly review.\"}\n- If your feature budget will be exceeded, submit a budget exception request.\n\n**New rate card:** v{new_effective_date.strftime('%Y%m%d')} \u2014 available in the service catalogue.\n\nQuestions? Reply to this email or open a ticket tagged `finops-rate-card`.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    return RateCardNotification(\n        subject=f\"[FinOps] Rate Card Update \u2014 {new_effective_date} (provider price change)\",\n        body_md=body,\n        channels=[NotificationChannel.EMAIL, NotificationChannel.SLACK],\n        recipients=[\"finops-announce@company.internal\"],\n        send_at=new_effective_date,\n    )\n\ndef build_quarterly_notification(\n    version: int,\n    effective_date: date,\n    impact_rows: list[TeamImpactRow],\n    markup_changes: list[str],\n) -> RateCardNotification:\n    total_annual = sum(r.annual_delta_usd for r in impact_rows)\n    material_teams = [r.team for r in impact_rows if abs(r.delta_pct) > 0.05]\n\n    body = f\"\"\"## Quarterly Rate Card Update \u2014 v{version} Effective {effective_date}\n\nThis is the scheduled quarterly update to the internal GenAI rate card.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n{chr(10).join(f\"- {c}\" for c in markup_changes) if markup_changes else \"- No markup changes this quarter.\"}\n\n**Portfolio impact:** ${total_annual:+,.0f} annual (all teams combined)\n\n**Teams with > 5% spend change:** {\", \".join(material_teams) if material_teams else \"None\"}\n\n**Timeline:**\n- Today: Notification sent (T-14)\n- {effective_date}: New rates take effect\n- {effective_date} + 7 days: Adoption confirmation report\n\n**New rate card:** v{version} published in the service catalogue and FinOps dashboard.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    return RateCardNotification(\n        subject=f\"[FinOps] Quarterly Rate Card v{version} \u2014 Effective {effective_date}\",\n        body_md=body,\n        channels=[NotificationChannel.EMAIL, NotificationChannel.SLACK, NotificationChannel.TICKET],\n        recipients=[\"all-engineering@company.internal\", \"finance@company.internal\"],\n        send_at=effective_date,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
