      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Post-Cutover Adoption Verification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After a new rate card goes live, confirm that all API calls are being charged at the new version. A single gateway instance reading a stale cached rate card can silently under-charge or over-charge for hours. Check adoption within 24 hours of the cutover."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import sqlite3\n\ndef verify_rate_card_adoption(\n    db: sqlite3.Connection,\n    new_version: int,\n    check_date: date,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    After a new card goes live, confirm all charges are using the new version.\n    Looks at the 24 hours following the effective date.\n    \"\"\"\"\n    row = db.execute(\"\"\"        SELECT\n            COUNT(*) AS total_calls,\n            SUM(CASE WHEN rate_card_version = ? THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS new_version_calls,\n            SUM(CASE WHEN rate_card_version != ? THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS stale_calls,\n            COUNT(DISTINCT team) AS teams_with_calls\n        FROM llm_call_log\n        WHERE DATE(timestamp) = ?\n    \"\"\", (new_version, new_version, check_date.isoformat())).fetchone()\n\n    adoption_pct = row[\"new_version_calls\"] / row[\"total_calls\"] if row[\"total_calls\"] else 0.0\n    return {\n        \"date\": check_date.isoformat(),\n        \"new_version\": new_version,\n        \"total_calls\": row[\"total_calls\"],\n        \"adoption_pct\": adoption_pct,\n        \"stale_calls\": row[\"stale_calls\"],\n        \"teams_with_calls\": row[\"teams_with_calls\"],\n        \"status\": \"OK\" if adoption_pct >= 0.99 else \"NEEDS_INVESTIGATION\",\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Tag every LLM call log row with the rate card version used at charge time. This makes the adoption query exact and gives a clean audit trail if a team disputes charges during the transition window."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Disputes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
