      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rate card updates require two parallel processes: a reactive track (5 business days) for material provider price changes and a quarterly scheduled track (30 days) for all other updates. Both tracks start with automated impact analysis that quantifies the annual cost delta per team before any notification goes out. Notification templates are audience-specific: engineering leads get action items, finance gets GL-level impact, product managers get budget headroom. Post-cutover adoption verification confirms all gateways switched to the new version within 24 hours, and a clear dispute-resolution path prevents retrospective billing arguments from becoming team-level conflicts."
          }
        ]
      }
